parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pressure hose can cause a loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Power steering fluid leaks
difficulty steering
increased effort required to steer
noise or vibration when steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front skidplate bolt can cause damage to the vehicle's underside and potentially lead to loss of control or accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Broken or loose front skidplate bolt
noise or rattling from the underside of the vehicle
potential damage to surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof glass can cause a loud noise, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries from flying glass.
symptoms: Loud popping or shattering sound
rattling noise
shattered glass
sudden and unexpected failure of the sunroof glass.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission coolant line can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature wear and potential failure, which can result in costly repairs and potentially leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Internal leak in the transmission coolant line
transmission overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, even when parked on an incline, which can lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle or surrounding property.
symptoms: Parking brake will not engage
vehicle continues to roll or move when parked on an incline
parking brake pedal can be pushed all the way to the floorboard and will not engage
vehicle moves forward in neutral when the parking brake is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag system malfunction can lead to a false sense of security, as the airbag light may indicate a faulty system, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light remains illuminated on the dashboard
despite multiple repairs by the dealer
indicating a faulty airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Rear Door Handle Motor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear door handle motor can cause the rear hatch to open unintentionally, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The rear hatch opens unexpectedly while driving or parked
the rear door handle motor is corroded
the rear door handle is malfunctioning.
